columns.name: Case Number
columns.description: The tracking number used to refer to this application or permit record in various DPD tracking systems.

columns.name: Case Type
columns.description: Type of activity investigated by the case (Housing/Zoning case, Unfit Buildings, etc.)

columns.name: Address
columns.description: Street address of the case investigation.

columns.name: Description
columns.description: A brief description of the proposed scope for the case.

columns.name: Case Group
columns.description: The sub-type of the Case. For example, a “HOUSING” type of CITATION, etc.

columns.name: Date Case Created
columns.description: The date that the case was opened. (This date may have been preceded by inspections on an allegation, with the case opened only after determining that a violation exists).

columns.name: Last Inspection Date
columns.description: The date of the last Compliance inspection so far.

columns.name: Last Inspection Result
columns.description: The result of the last Compliance inspection so far. Note that a “Failed” inspection may result when even a single item is not yet in compliance

columns.name: Status
columns.description: Indicates the type of compliance achieved, or the final outcome of the case. “Open” indicates that work is still in progress to achieve compliance.

columns.name: Permit and Complaint Status URL
columns.description: Link to view full details and current status information about this permit at DPD’s website

columns.name: Latitude
columns.description: Latitude of the address where the case is being investigated.

columns.name: Longitude
columns.description: Longitude of the address where the case is being investigated.

columns.name: Location
columns.description: Mapping coordinates of the address where the case is being investigated.
